g.text: Inland Empire: Awful lonely here. No ruckus. No old men playing their little ball game.
Inland Empire: No need to beat yourself down over it. It probably wasn't the definitive piece of the puzzle. Still, somehow it feels like May bells matter somehow.
You: "Wait, maybe they died during the mercenary tribunal?"
Maybe they too died during the mercenary tribunal?
You: "Damn, I missed asking these guys about the dried May bells."
Damn. Looks like I missed asking these guys about the dried May bells.
You: "But what if I wanted to talk to them?"
You: Yeah, where did they go?

Kim Kitsuragi: "And, I mean... it would be one twist too many if it turned out these two old men were our killers. That's just unlikely. No..." He seems pleased with himself. "We would only have wasted our time here."
Empathy: The lieutenant is thinking of all the time you've spared. He likes it.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Don't beat yourself up about it. I think I gave you a pretty exhaustive answer about those flowers and what they mean."
You: Yeah, where did the old guys go?
You: That's just how craters are. [Discard thought.]
Inland Empire: *Still* you can't shake the feeling that somehow these may bell do actually matter. If only a little bit.
Logic: It was probably nothing anyway. Just a little thought you had.
Inland Empire: Home? To work? To get something from somewhere? Who knows what people are doing when we're not looking.
Kim Kitsuragi: "They didn't," the lieutenant calms you. "Trust me. I saw the bodies."
Physical Instrument: Enough with the goddamn flowers already! Are you a cop or a florist?
Kim Kitsuragi: "You mean the guys who were playing pétanque?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Have you noticed people sometimes appear and disappear in places? It's called *doing things*."
Inland Empire: It's very unlikely. Everyone scattered once the tribunal started. They're probably fine.
Kim Kitsuragi: "You'll get them next time," the lieutenant replies, looking at the empty crater.
Inland Empire: You'll get them next time. But let's be honest, they weren't even in the suspects list.
Inland Empire: You would have wasted *so* much time talking to these two pensioners. Precious case-time.
